Well, since this is the thread to disclose.  Here goes.<br>
Chet Botkins, served in country from October 65 until May  67.  Shipped from Ft. Lewis, Wa. with the 4th Inf. Div. via troop transport.  The 4th got sent to Pleiku and our tracks got assigned to the 1st Cav. Spent the first year with the Ist Cav. in An Khe.  Battallion Radio Repairman for an 8 inch arty Batt.  Spent second part with the 9th Inf. in Chu Lai.  Where the Americal Div. was formed up.<br>
Married same woman 26 yrs.  Same job 27 years. Technical Trainer for a large copier company. Anyone that has seen my posts has my e-mail address and has permission to use it to chat.<br>

